value: Now breeds from British Columbia to the west shore of Hudson Bay and locally to Wyoming; in winter south to southern California and Texas and casually further east.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Ponds, lakes, marshes, and slow-moving rivers, especially where reeds, sedges, or similar emergent vegetation that provide nesting habitat, occasionally in brackish situations; winters on open lakes and bays, occasionally ponds, and often feeds in agricultural fields.
